OL,3,CCarer who helped husband play football
OL,4,Cagain after brain injury up for award
OL,6,FReporter Tom Barton went to meet Dave
OL,7,FGiles and his wife Sue, who has been
OL,8,Fnominated for a national award for her
OL,9,Fwork as his carer
OL,11,FA Newcastle carer who helped her
OL,12,Ffootball-loving husband play again
OL,13,Ffollowing a brain injury has been
OL,14,Fnominated for a national award.
OL,16,FSue Giles, 65, has cared for her 69-
OL,17,Fyear-old husband Dave for the last 18
OL,18,Fyears in a range of ways, including
OL,19,Fassisting him during walking football
OL,20,Fsessions.
